latestPosts.caption:
A Moment of Pride & Recognition #IIFA2025

As we celebrate 25 glorious years of the International IIFA, we are deeply honored to receive this special message from Hon’ble Prime Minister Narendra Modi, recognizing IIFA’s journey and its role in taking Indian cinema to the world. 🇮🇳🌍

IIFA is a proudly Indian, homegrown brand that has transcended borders, uniting cultures and audiences across the globe. Connecting over 2 billion people annually, it’s a true phenomenon.

Over the years, it has showcased the best of Indian cinema on an international stage, creating opportunities for artists, filmmakers, and businesses. This milestone 25th edition is extra special as we proudly bring IIFA back home to India, in Jaipur for a celebration of our cinematic excellence in the land where it all began. 

Hosting IIFA in India once again allows us to showcase its immense economic and cultural impact and welcoming new visitors, boosting tourism, and opening doors for film production, business, and trade.

Beyond the glamour, an event of this scale transforms cities, driving tourism, hospitality, film production, and local economies. Over the years, IIFA has elevated global destinations, inspiring filmmakers to explore new locations, attracting international attention, and reinforcing India’s position as a powerhouse of entertainment and culture. 

Thank you to every filmmaker, artist, musician, and technician who has been part of this journey. This is your moment.

Join us as we celebrate with the biggest names in Indian cinema, creating history once again! 

Don’t miss the IIFA Awards – airing this Sunday, 16th March, 8pm onwards only on Zee TV!

#NarendraModi #IIFA2025 #IIFAJaipur
